                     <scopecontent id="aspace_48c5e484ed551cb4c40c95180bab42bb">
                        <head>Scope and Contents</head>
                        <p>Informational brochure. CHIEA opened its Faculty of Theology with 21 students on September 3, 1984 and was formally inaugurated by Pope John Paul II on August 18, 1985. Its chief objectives were to become a fully-fledged Catholic university, to become a center of research and publications in theology and related subjects, and to advance ecumenism through dialogue with other Christian churches.</p>
